'''Irene Maguire''' was an [[United States|American]] [[Figure skating|figure skater]]. She competed in [[Pair skating|pairs]] and [[ice dancing|ice dance]] with [[Walter Muehlbronner]], whom she married in 1951. They won national silver medals in both pairs and ice dance in 1949 and 1950.<ref name=resultsbook>[http://www.skatecanada.ca/en/events_results/results/archives/SkateCanadaResultsBook-%20Volume1-1896-1973.pdf ''Results Book'' Skate Canada]</ref> The two continued skating as professionals, billed as "Walter and Irene" for 7 years, in the [[Ice Follies]].<ref name=walterobit1>[http://www.chestnuthilllocal.com/issues/2005.11.24/obituaries.html "Obituaries", Chestnut Hill Local]</ref><ref>"Youngsters Formed Skating Team, Now in Ice Follies", [[Christian Science Monitor]], Feb 11, 1953 [http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/csmonitor_historic/access/221510532.html?dids=221510532:221510532&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:AI&date=Feb+11,+1953&author=&pub=Christian+Science+Monitor&desc=Youngsters+Formed+Skating+Team,+Now+in+Ice+Follies&pqatl=google]</ref><ref>"Obituary: Skating club manager, 83", [[Philadelphia Inquirer]], November 19, 2005 [http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=PI&s_site=philly&p_multi=PI&p_theme=realcities&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=10DFFDA8EC8F7498&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM]</ref>
